Reform is a change that you're supposed to like. So as soon as you hear the word
reform you can reach for your wallet and see who's lifting it. [...] Subsidy is
another interesting word, kind of like reform. It's a subsidy if public funds
are used for public purposes. That's called a subsidy. It's not called a subsidy
when it goes to private wealth. That's reform or something.

        -- Noam Chomsky, talk titled "Free Market Fantasies" at Harvard
