%
Suppose you walk out in the street, this evening, and you see a crime being
committed, you know, somebody is robbing someone else. Well, you have three
choices. One choice is to try to stop it, maybe you call 911 or something.
Another choice is to do nothing. A third choice is to pick up an assault rifle
and kill 'em both, and kill a bystander at the same time. Well, suppose you do
that, and somebody says, "Well, you know, why did you do that?" And you say,
"Look, I couldn't stand by and do nothing." I mean, is that a response?

        -- Noam Chomsky

