Yet to enter approved memory is the "finale" described in the official Air Force
history, a 1000-plane raid on civilian targets organized by General "Hap" Arnold
to celebrate the war's end, five days after Nagasaki. According to survivors,
leaflets were dropped among the bombs announcing the surrender.

