If I were to summarize the main points I’ve taken from Chomsky’s writings and
talks, they would be this: You should have both compassion and consistency, care
about freedom and fairness alike, and be rational, curious, and humble.

        -- Nathan J. Robinson, "Lessons from Chomsky"
           in Current Affairs, December 2018
           https://www.currentaffairs.org/2018/12/lessons-from-chomsky

%
It is a tribute to the power of Chomsky’s political views and the evidence he
presents in their support that so many critics of his politics feel that the
best strategy for undermining them is to attack his linguistics.

        -- "1000 Ways to Misrepresent Noam Chomsky"
           Current Affairs, December 2016
           https://www.currentaffairs.org/2016/12/thousand-ways-to-misrepresent-noam-chomsky

